101
00:07:24,007 --> 00:07:26,634
[lecturer through earbuds] When the heart
rate drops to 40 bpm or lower,

102
00:07:26,718 --> 00:07:30,346
one may experience lightheadedness,
syncope, or loss of consciousness.

103
00:07:31,014 --> 00:07:32,932
-However, ironically enough…
-[sighs]

104
00:07:33,016 --> 00:07:35,310
…the heart fights to keep beating
until the very end.

105
00:07:51,743 --> 00:07:55,413
While chest pain is the most common
early symptom of a myocardial infarction,

106
00:07:55,497 --> 00:07:58,500
women and diabetics
may display atypical symptoms

107
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:03,880
such as shortness of breath,
indigestion, or severe fatigue.

108
00:08:04,464 --> 00:08:07,550
Moreover, around 20 to 30%
of patients experience

109
00:08:07,634 --> 00:08:09,719
myocardial infarctions
without any early signs.

110
00:08:09,803 --> 00:08:11,679
So, for an accurate diagnosis, they must…

111
00:08:26,778 --> 00:08:28,154
You didn't have to do that.

112
00:08:37,831 --> 00:08:38,832
Oh.

113
00:08:41,084 --> 00:08:43,461
Hey, you got a minute?

114
00:08:44,587 --> 00:08:46,256
Thanks for the drink.

115
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:51,845
You're all by yourself again.

116
00:08:53,179 --> 00:08:54,597
Why are you always alone?

117
00:08:57,559 --> 00:09:02,105
You study alone, eat alone,
drink coffee alone…

118
00:09:04,732 --> 00:09:07,193
-It's just comfortable.
-Mmm.

119
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,822
Are you just used to being alone?

120
00:09:11,406 --> 00:09:13,449
Or do you have to be alone
to feel comfortable?

121
00:09:20,331 --> 00:09:22,292
I'll see you around, Taeju.

122
00:09:23,877 --> 00:09:24,878
Hold on.

123
00:09:28,673 --> 00:09:30,133
How do you know my name?

124
00:09:36,431 --> 00:09:38,057
KANG TAEJU

125
00:09:40,393 --> 00:09:41,394
[sighs]

126
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:53,031
[♪ romantic music playing]

127
00:10:04,584 --> 00:10:06,294
[lecturer] Heart rate.

128
00:10:06,878 --> 00:10:11,216
When resting, the human heart beats
around 60 to 100 times per minute.

129
00:10:11,299 --> 00:10:13,301
This is called the resting heart rate.

130
00:10:13,384 --> 00:10:17,138
However, the heart rate may
exceed 100 bpm and remain elevated,

131
00:10:17,222 --> 00:10:20,558
even without any physical activity
or external stimulus.

132
00:10:21,434 --> 00:10:23,937
This is called tachycardia.

133
00:10:25,104 --> 00:10:27,690
On the other hand,
when the heart rate is 60 bpm or lower,

134
00:10:27,774 --> 00:10:29,442
it's called bradycardia.

135
00:10:29,525 --> 00:10:32,779
Both can be signs
of underlying conditions,

136
00:10:32,862 --> 00:10:36,366
including cardiac disorders,
such as arrhythmia or thyroid dysfunction,

137
00:10:36,449 --> 00:10:38,326
so one must be wary of both symptoms.

138
00:10:40,578 --> 00:10:46,042
That said, what is the most common
physical symptom a patient notices

139
00:10:46,125 --> 00:10:50,004
when their heart beats at an abnormal rate
due to tachycardia or bradycardia?

140
00:11:05,645 --> 00:11:06,646
[lecturer] Well…
STYLE
::cue()

141
00:11:08,273 --> 00:11:10,191
their heart races.

142
00:11:20,076 --> 00:11:21,911
I'm sharing your umbrella.

143
00:11:23,621 --> 00:11:24,622
How have you been?

144
00:11:26,165 --> 00:11:27,542
What's been going on with you?

145
00:11:28,501 --> 00:11:29,585
What do you mean?

146
00:11:31,963 --> 00:11:34,507
Where have you been for the past few days?

147
00:11:37,468 --> 00:11:38,594
Why do you ask?

148
00:11:39,387 --> 00:11:40,513
I mean, you know.

149
00:11:42,098 --> 00:11:44,475
I was used to seeing you around every day.

150
00:11:45,184 --> 00:11:46,686
So it got me wondering.

151
00:11:50,231 --> 00:11:51,566
Oh. [giggles]

152
00:11:52,692 --> 00:11:55,028
I was stuck at home with the flu for days.

153
00:11:55,111 --> 00:11:57,155
I actually thought I was going to die.

154
00:11:59,907 --> 00:12:00,908
Flu?

155
00:12:01,492 --> 00:12:02,493
So that's what it was.

156
00:12:03,661 --> 00:12:05,872
-Are you better now?
-Yeah, much better.

157
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,833
Were you worried about me?

158
00:12:13,838 --> 00:12:15,965
I was pretty worried about you.

159
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:18,551
What?

160
00:12:19,302 --> 00:12:20,887
As I was lying in bed,

161
00:12:21,679 --> 00:12:25,433
