248
00:18:53,612 --> 00:18:55,948
How dare he do this to my daughter!

249
00:18:57,992 --> 00:18:59,994
Despicable piece of shit.

250
00:19:02,413 --> 00:19:05,541
I swear to God, I'll rip him to pieces!

251
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:07,418
-[grunts]
-[sighs]

252
00:19:07,501 --> 00:19:09,336
[panting] This can't be happening.

253
00:19:11,172 --> 00:19:12,506
Kidnapping?

254
00:19:12,590 --> 00:19:13,716
Blackmail?

255
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:16,218
[gasps]

256
00:19:16,302 --> 00:19:19,513
How could this
be happening to my daughter?

257
00:19:20,598 --> 00:19:21,932
But why?

258
00:19:25,102 --> 00:19:27,229
Is this all he sent?

259
00:19:28,481 --> 00:19:29,482
[Seyun's mother groans]

260
00:19:31,442 --> 00:19:32,985
[groans]

261
00:19:37,072 --> 00:19:38,407
You got nothing else?

262
00:19:59,762 --> 00:20:01,430
UNKNOWN NUMBER

263
00:20:03,974 --> 00:20:05,059
DELETE

264
00:20:09,355 --> 00:20:10,356
[rings]

265
00:20:11,065 --> 00:20:13,317
[Dr. Ko] Two billion won in two hours…

266
00:20:16,487 --> 00:20:17,738
Did he demand anything else?

267
00:20:20,908 --> 00:20:24,203
He said he'd hurt Seyun
if we went to the police.

268
00:20:24,912 --> 00:20:27,081
We can't get them involved,
no matter what.

269
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:30,292
[grunts]

270
00:20:31,710 --> 00:20:33,420
How much time do we have left?

271
00:20:33,504 --> 00:20:36,382
Oh, uh, we've got around
an hour and 25 minutes.

272
00:20:36,465 --> 00:20:37,466
[gasps]

273
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:40,427
We have to hurry.
I'll make calls to banks.

274
00:20:40,511 --> 00:20:42,805
You take the car and pick up the money.

275
00:20:43,806 --> 00:20:46,517
He may come after the money again,
so you go with him.

276
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,227
Oh, yes. Of course.

277
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:50,229
Okay, we'll be back.

278
00:20:50,855 --> 00:20:52,857
-Wait, honey. Just a sec.
-Huh?

279
00:20:52,940 --> 00:20:55,651
[whispers] Come here for a minute.

280
00:20:58,612 --> 00:20:59,905
[whispering indistinctly]

281
00:21:01,991 --> 00:21:04,076
I'll ask them to arrange that.

282
00:21:04,159 --> 00:21:06,036
[whispering continues]

283
00:21:07,288 --> 00:21:08,497
[whispers] Got it.

284
00:21:10,165 --> 00:21:14,420
-Yes, hello? Is this the bank manager?
-We'll take my car.

285
00:21:59,757 --> 00:22:02,092
Father, I have to tell you something.

286
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:05,095
-The thing is--
-It's you.

287
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:07,389
This is your fault, isn't it?

288
00:22:10,351 --> 00:22:11,352
What is?

289
00:22:11,435 --> 00:22:13,812
This has to be happening because of you.

290
00:22:14,939 --> 00:22:17,983
What are you… What do you mean by that?

291
00:22:18,734 --> 00:22:22,321
Seyun isn't the type
to go around making enemies.

292
00:22:22,404 --> 00:22:27,284
You were probably acting all arrogant
and crossed the wrong person. Am I right?

293
00:22:28,953 --> 00:22:30,663
You were like that in the past too.

294
00:22:30,746 --> 00:22:33,499
You don't care about anything else
when you think you're right.

295
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:36,293
You can't have changed.

296
00:22:38,462 --> 00:22:39,588
[sighs]

297
00:22:42,841 --> 00:22:44,635
Well, say something!

298
00:22:45,177 --> 00:22:47,805
I'm asking you
if that's why this is happening!

299
00:22:48,514 --> 00:22:49,515
Damn it!

300
00:22:49,598 --> 00:22:51,016
-[tires screech]
-[Dr. Ko] That piece of…

301
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:52,309
[horn honks]

302
00:22:52,393 --> 00:22:53,811
Crazy bastard.

303
00:22:55,229 --> 00:22:56,522
Give me a break.

304
00:22:57,231 --> 00:22:58,732
Seriously…

305
00:22:59,608 --> 00:23:00,985
[moaning]

306
00:23:07,992 --> 00:23:10,077
[sobbing]
STYLE
::cue()

307
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,213
Come on…

308
00:23:22,798 --> 00:23:24,008
[grunts]

309
00:23:29,430 --> 00:23:30,431
[Dr. Ko sighs]

310
00:23:56,582 --> 00:23:58,083
[door lock beeping]

311
00:24:00,294 --> 00:24:01,420
[sighs]

312
00:24:04,673 --> 00:24:09,053
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

313
00:24:09,136 --> 00:24:11,180
[♪ ominous music playing]

314
00:24:19,521 --> 00:24:20,647
[officer] How are you?

315
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:24,568
I'm Jang Dosik, Captain
of Major Crimes Unit 1 at Seongjin Police.

316
00:24:24,651 --> 00:24:26,987
I've got a few questions for you.

317
00:24:27,071 --> 00:24:29,239
We don't have much time,
so if you don't mind.

318
00:24:31,158 --> 00:24:32,951
So the kidnapper got in your car,

319
00:24:33,035 --> 00:24:36,455
pretending to be your designated driver,
at around 1:30 a.m.

320
00:24:36,538 --> 00:24:40,042
I feel like I made the call a second ago.
You got here so quickly.

321
00:24:40,125 --> 00:24:43,587
[driver] Well, I just happened to be
in the area, so I got here fast.

322
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:48,258
I guess today's just my lucky day.

323
00:24:48,884 --> 00:24:50,761
[Dosik] Remember what the culprit
looked like?

324
00:24:50,844 --> 00:24:53,722
Any scars, tattoos, or anything
we could use to identify him?

325
00:24:55,099 --> 00:24:57,518
No, nothing really comes to mind.

326
00:24:59,978 --> 00:25:02,606
[Dosik] And you didn't recognize
his voice either?

327
00:25:03,732 --> 00:25:05,150
[Taeju] Hello?

328
00:25:05,234 --> 00:25:06,860
[driver] Mr. Kang Taeju?

329
00:25:07,528 --> 00:25:08,946
Yes, speaking. Who's this?

330
00:25:09,029 --> 00:25:10,906
I'm the driver
who drove you to your house.

331
00:25:10,989 --> 00:25:11,990
UNKNOWN NUMBER

332
00:25:12,074 --> 00:25:14,409
Well, early this morning, sir.

333
00:25:14,493 --> 00:25:16,578
I'd never heard his voice before.

334
00:25:17,663 --> 00:25:18,747
And his face…

335
00:25:20,749 --> 00:25:24,086
I don't really remember
what he looks like either.

336
00:25:26,463 --> 00:25:27,464
-Choi.
-Yes, sir?

337
00:25:27,548 --> 00:25:29,800
Secure the security footage
around the area.

338
00:25:29,883 --> 00:25:30,884
[Hyeonsu] I'm on it.

339
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:35,472
[Dosik] The kidnapper could call
any minute now.

340
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,684
We'll be tracking his location
in real time,

341
00:25:38,767 --> 00:25:41,520
so try to drag it out as much as possible.

342
00:25:41,603 --> 00:25:44,565
Culprits like him
like to feel like they're in charge,

343
00:25:44,648 --> 00:25:46,942
so try not to provoke him in any way.

344
00:25:47,985 --> 00:25:49,695
-[Taeju] Okay.
-As for you two,

345
00:25:49,778 --> 00:25:51,655
never interfere or get worked up.

346
00:25:51,738 --> 00:25:54,491
If he catches on,
it'll put your daughter in danger.

347
00:25:54,575 --> 00:25:56,326
[both sigh]

348
00:25:57,327 --> 00:25:58,537
Understood.

349
00:25:58,620 --> 00:26:00,664
[Dosik] I appreciate your cooperation.

350
00:26:08,422 --> 00:26:10,299
Why did you call the police?

351
00:26:11,175 --> 00:26:13,844
I told you it would put Seyun in danger.

352
00:26:14,469 --> 00:26:16,013
I thought I'd made that clear.

353
00:26:16,597 --> 00:26:19,725
What, are we supposed to listen
to whatever this guy says?

354
00:26:20,475 --> 00:26:24,479
Of course he tells you not to call them.
He doesn't want to get caught.

355
00:26:25,689 --> 00:26:28,192
You don't understand.
This guy is extremely dangerous.

356
00:26:28,275 --> 00:26:30,527
That's why we called the police.

357
00:26:31,111 --> 00:26:33,030
You're not getting it. This guy…

358
00:26:34,573 --> 00:26:37,159
He's completely insane.

359
00:26:41,872 --> 00:26:44,750
He's a total psycho.

360
00:26:44,833 --> 00:26:47,586
All the more reason we need the police.

361
00:26:47,669 --> 00:26:49,671
We can't deal with him on our own.

362
00:26:49,755 --> 00:26:50,964
No, you don't get it!

363
00:26:51,048 --> 00:26:52,174
[gasps]

364
00:26:52,257 --> 00:26:54,927
You're just putting Seyun
in more danger right now!

365
00:26:55,010 --> 00:26:57,930
You will not speak to my wife that way!

366
00:26:59,765 --> 00:27:01,391
She's my own daughter.

367
00:27:01,975 --> 00:27:02,976
You got that?

368
00:27:03,852 --> 00:27:06,730
I'm the one
who's the most desperate to get her back!

369
00:27:10,609 --> 00:27:11,610
Listen, Taeju.

370
00:27:12,402 --> 00:27:15,072
You've been in the palm of his hand,

371
00:27:15,155 --> 00:27:16,990
so you aren't thinking straight.

372
00:27:17,616 --> 00:27:20,285
This is where you have to
let us handle things.

373
00:27:20,869 --> 00:27:22,329
And don't get in the way!

374
00:27:22,412 --> 00:27:25,415
You have no idea what this guy's like.

375
00:27:27,876 --> 00:27:30,420
You just don't know
because you haven't dealt with him.

376
00:27:31,088 --> 00:27:33,256
Sir? I know this is tough,

377
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:35,842
but you need to stay calm.

378
00:27:36,468 --> 00:27:37,469
Okay?

379
00:27:38,595 --> 00:27:39,596
Yeah.

380
00:27:42,808 --> 00:27:44,101
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

381
00:27:45,394 --> 00:27:46,520
[grunts]

382
00:27:47,813 --> 00:27:48,897
[grunts]

383
00:27:54,778 --> 00:27:55,862
[grunts]

384
00:27:56,446 --> 00:27:58,031
-[metal scraping]
-[grunting]

385
00:28:20,095 --> 00:28:21,096
Anyone there?

386
00:28:21,179 --> 00:28:23,890
Please let me out of here!

387
00:28:23,974 --> 00:28:25,934
Let me out of here!

388
00:28:29,187 --> 00:28:30,313
Hey!

389
00:28:30,814 --> 00:28:32,149
[sobbing]

390
00:28:42,909 --> 00:28:44,369
[person] Are you okay?

391
00:28:48,457 --> 00:28:50,042
Are you hurt at all?

392
00:28:52,169 --> 00:28:53,587
Who's there?

393
00:28:54,713 --> 00:28:56,590
[person] I bet you're pretty confused.

394
00:28:59,426 --> 00:29:00,552
Who the hell are you?

395
00:29:01,344 --> 00:29:02,345
What do you want?

396
00:29:03,013 --> 00:29:06,641
[person] Don't make loud noises.
You'll be in trouble.

397
00:29:10,479 --> 00:29:13,315
-What the hell are you saying?
-[person shushes]

398
00:29:14,232 --> 00:29:18,028
Be quiet! You'll get us both in trouble.

399
00:29:21,073 --> 00:29:22,199
Huh?

400
00:29:27,579 --> 00:29:29,289
[metal scraping]

401
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:39,800
Hey.

402
00:29:42,094 --> 00:29:44,096
Excuse me, what did you just say?

403
00:29:45,138 --> 00:29:48,517
[person] We'll get in trouble
with the guy who locked us up here.

404
00:29:51,895 --> 00:29:54,064
Are you locked up against your will too?

405
00:29:54,147 --> 00:29:55,982
[person sobbing]

406
00:29:59,861 --> 00:30:04,074
Hey, how long
have you been locked up in here?

407
00:30:04,157 --> 00:30:05,575
[person] There's no time.

408
00:30:05,659 --> 00:30:07,661
I'm running out of time.

409
00:30:09,162 --> 00:30:10,831
What does that mean?

410
00:30:12,082 --> 00:30:16,419
[person] When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…

411
00:30:17,170 --> 00:30:20,465
[crying] By the pale white snow…
It's all over for me.

412
00:30:20,549 --> 00:30:21,591
It's over.

413
00:30:23,844 --> 00:30:25,178
Hey.

414
00:30:26,221 --> 00:30:30,642
[person crying] Once she's completely
swallowed, I'll be done for.
STYLE
::cue()

415
00:30:36,982 --> 00:30:38,692
[Seyun sighs]

416
00:30:41,361 --> 00:30:42,571
[sniffles]

417
00:30:56,835 --> 00:31:00,130
He might video call you again,
so you'll sit here alone.

418
00:31:00,755 --> 00:31:02,215
-Hey, Park.
-Yes, sir.

419
00:31:04,009 --> 00:31:08,180
We'll be monitoring in real-time,
so just try to focus on the call.

420
00:31:08,263 --> 00:31:10,473
And try to drag it out
as long as possible.

421
00:31:11,224 --> 00:31:13,810
I know you're nervous,
but your wife's life is on the line.

422
00:31:14,394 --> 00:31:16,146
You have to keep it together, all right?

423
00:31:17,230 --> 00:31:19,191
-Yeah.
-Two minutes left.

424
00:31:19,274 --> 00:31:21,651
-Oh, take them to their room.
-[Park] On it.

425
00:31:21,735 --> 00:31:22,777
This way.

426
00:31:27,199 --> 00:31:29,326
Let's just focus on saving Seyun.

427
00:31:30,702 --> 00:31:32,787
-Okay?
-[Dr. Ko sighs]

428
00:31:36,041 --> 00:31:37,083
Don't mess this up.

429
00:31:38,793 --> 00:31:39,794
Yes, sir.

430
00:32:00,023 --> 00:32:02,067
[♪ tense music playing]

431
00:32:19,125 --> 00:32:20,961
[beeping]

432
00:32:24,214 --> 00:32:26,424
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

433
00:32:26,508 --> 00:32:27,842
[phone buzzing]

434
00:32:32,138 --> 00:32:34,683
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

435
00:32:37,727 --> 00:32:38,728
Hello?

436
00:32:41,398 --> 00:32:42,482
It's you, isn't it?

437
00:32:43,817 --> 00:32:45,402
Where are you, Mr. Kang?

438
00:32:45,485 --> 00:32:48,071
Oh, I'm at my in-laws' house right now.

439
00:32:48,154 --> 00:32:49,531
In-laws?

440
00:32:49,614 --> 00:32:50,782
Yeah, I mean,

441
00:32:50,865 --> 00:32:55,120
they managed to prepare the money.

442
00:32:55,203 --> 00:32:57,956
And I didn't want to take off
with so much money.

443
00:32:58,039 --> 00:32:59,165
[tires screech]
STYLE
::cue()

444
00:33:13,471 --> 00:33:14,597
You got him?

445
00:33:14,681 --> 00:33:15,932
LIVE TRACKING MAP

446
00:33:16,016 --> 00:33:17,142
[whispering] He's in Mangok-dong.

447
00:33:18,184 --> 00:33:20,687
-Send the squad over to Mangok-dong.
-[Hyeonsu] Copy that.

448
00:33:21,354 --> 00:33:22,355
[sighs]

449
00:33:24,566 --> 00:33:26,067
-[beeping]
-Huh?

450
00:33:26,568 --> 00:33:27,944
What's going on?

451
00:33:29,571 --> 00:33:32,157
Something's wrong.
It says he's in Useong-dong now.

452
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:33,950
You said Mangok-dong.

453
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,161
He's moving again.

454
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:40,165
-He's in Jonghaeng-dong.
-What the hell are you talking about?

455
00:33:40,665 --> 00:33:43,084
He's bouncing the signal
with some kind of hacking tool.

456
00:33:43,168 --> 00:33:44,669
Well, do something about it!

457
00:33:53,636 --> 00:33:54,637
Hello?

458
00:33:56,097 --> 00:33:57,766
Anybody else at home?

459
00:33:59,059 --> 00:34:01,061
No, I'm here on my own.

460
00:34:02,437 --> 00:34:04,773
So you're the only one
on the line right now?

461
00:34:05,398 --> 00:34:06,483
[Taeju] Yes, that's right.

462
00:34:09,152 --> 00:34:10,987
So you're saying…

463
00:34:11,780 --> 00:34:14,949
I can say whatever I want,
since it's just you and me, right?

464
00:34:17,243 --> 00:34:18,244
Yeah, I'd say so.

465
00:34:18,953 --> 00:34:22,290
But first, don't you want to see the cash?

466
00:34:22,374 --> 00:34:23,375
Mr. Kang.

467
00:34:23,458 --> 00:34:25,210
Take a look. It's all here.

468
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:29,047
No messing around this time.
I got it all in cash right…

469
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:30,715
Mr. Kang Taeju!

470
00:34:37,055 --> 00:34:39,224
-Yeah.
-[driver panting]

471
00:34:45,021 --> 00:34:46,773
Switch to the back camera for me.

472
00:34:48,566 --> 00:34:49,901
But why?

473
00:34:50,693 --> 00:34:52,987
Just switch it for me, all right?

474
00:35:00,203 --> 00:35:01,329
There you go.

475
00:35:06,334 --> 00:35:09,462
We're going to go through every nook
and cranny in the house.

476
00:35:10,338 --> 00:35:11,923
Do as I tell you.

477
00:35:17,846 --> 00:35:19,389
Okay, right there.

478
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:22,100
Pan from left to right.

479
00:35:23,017 --> 00:35:24,060
Okay.

480
00:35:28,481 --> 00:35:30,275
What are you doing? Just do it.

481
00:35:34,821 --> 00:35:37,031
Okay, panning from left to right.

482
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:48,668
And the other way.

483
00:35:52,922 --> 00:35:53,923
[object thuds]

484
00:35:56,593 --> 00:35:57,635
Stop.

485
00:35:59,179 --> 00:36:00,930
What was that noise?

486
00:36:02,223 --> 00:36:04,142
What? I didn't hear anything.

487
00:36:04,809 --> 00:36:06,644
Did you not hear that noise?

488
00:36:08,438 --> 00:36:09,689
No, I didn't.

489
00:36:13,818 --> 00:36:14,903
Oh, is that so?

490
00:36:18,072 --> 00:36:19,866
Turn it to your right.

491
00:36:20,492 --> 00:36:21,826
Okay.

492
00:36:22,535 --> 00:36:24,370
That's your left, boss.

493
00:36:24,454 --> 00:36:28,082
Your right is toward the kitchen,
where the noise came from.

494
00:36:33,171 --> 00:36:34,172
[whispers] Oh dear…

495
00:36:44,057 --> 00:36:46,810
Keep pointing it that way
and walk toward it.
STYLE
::cue()

496
00:36:49,229 --> 00:36:50,313
Okay, got it.

497
00:37:15,421 --> 00:37:16,422
Stop.

498
00:37:25,348 --> 00:37:26,349
Mr. Kang.

499
00:37:28,268 --> 00:37:30,311
Now, turn to your right.

500
00:37:50,039 --> 00:37:51,666
I said, turn around.

501
00:38:04,512 --> 00:38:05,722
[door opens]

502
00:38:05,805 --> 00:38:08,600
-Good Lord. I can't stand this anymore.
-Honey.

503
00:38:09,392 --> 00:38:12,770
[Dr. Ko] Look, kid. Are you trying
to get my daughter back or not?

504
00:38:12,854 --> 00:38:14,397
[Seyun's mother] Honey, don't do this.

505
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:16,149
We said we'd let him handle it.

506
00:38:16,232 --> 00:38:17,358
[Dr. Ko] Quiet!

507
00:38:18,401 --> 00:38:19,903
-Give me that phone.
-[sighs]

508
00:38:22,113 --> 00:38:24,449
This is Seyun's father.

509
00:38:24,532 --> 00:38:26,284
-The girl you took away.
-[whispering]

510
00:38:26,367 --> 00:38:29,162
I was going to hand
my son-in-law the money

511
00:38:29,245 --> 00:38:31,247
and stay quiet in the other room,

512
00:38:31,331 --> 00:38:34,417
but I can't trust him with this anymore.

513
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:37,253
So from now on, you can talk to me.

514
00:38:38,421 --> 00:38:39,672
[driver] Put him back on.

515
00:38:40,256 --> 00:38:42,091
Trust me, young man.

516
00:38:42,175 --> 00:38:44,844
It'd be much easier if you talked to me.

517
00:38:45,887 --> 00:38:49,849
This deal is between Mr. Kang and me,
and he's the only one I'll speak to.

518
00:38:49,933 --> 00:38:52,310
Well, it's my daughter and my money!

519
00:38:52,393 --> 00:38:54,354
I'd listen if I were you.

520
00:38:54,437 --> 00:38:56,314
You can talk to me, all right?

521
00:38:56,397 --> 00:38:57,774
[exhales] Hey, old man!

522
00:38:57,857 --> 00:38:59,484
What? "Old man"?

523
00:38:59,567 --> 00:39:01,235
I said put Mr. Kang back on.

524
00:39:01,319 --> 00:39:03,905
You little… Look here, punk!

525
00:39:03,988 --> 00:39:06,824
I get that you're a criminal,
but show some respect!

526
00:39:06,908 --> 00:39:08,618
How dare you!

527
00:39:08,701 --> 00:39:10,578
What the hell…

528
00:39:11,245 --> 00:39:12,956
Have you lost your mind, pops?

529
00:39:13,039 --> 00:39:15,375
What did you call me?

530
00:39:15,458 --> 00:39:18,044
You little… How dare you!

531
00:39:18,127 --> 00:39:22,173
Uh, sir? Why don't you talk to me?

532
00:39:22,882 --> 00:39:24,175
What do you want, lady?

533
00:39:25,426 --> 00:39:28,429
Fine, go on if you want
your precious daughter to die…

534
00:39:28,513 --> 00:39:31,224
[Seyun's mother]
Here's an extra billion won.

535
00:39:31,307 --> 00:39:33,601
If you let my daughter go,

536
00:39:33,685 --> 00:39:36,562
you can have this
on top of the original two billion.

537
00:39:36,646 --> 00:39:39,273
That's three billion won in total.

538
00:39:39,357 --> 00:39:43,277
Hold on, so if I bring you
your daughter right now,

539
00:39:43,361 --> 00:39:45,363
you'll give me three billion won?

540
00:39:45,446 --> 00:39:47,115
Yeah, that's right.

541
00:39:48,616 --> 00:39:51,536
But we want her back within an hour.

542
00:39:53,246 --> 00:39:54,330
After an hour,

543
00:39:55,081 --> 00:39:57,166
I'm taking off 100 million
every five minutes.

544
00:39:57,250 --> 00:39:58,292
No.

545
00:39:59,836 --> 00:40:01,462
So what you're saying is,

546
00:40:02,005 --> 00:40:04,215
if I just bring you your daughter
within the hour,

547
00:40:04,298 --> 00:40:08,136
that three billion won can all be mine?

548
00:40:08,219 --> 00:40:11,180
The final amount will
depend on what you decide to do.

549
00:40:11,764 --> 00:40:15,184
Uh… One hour, three billion?
[inhales sharply]

550
00:40:18,813 --> 00:40:21,024
I'll be in touch within an hour.

551
00:40:21,649 --> 00:40:23,651
I hope you keep your promise, ma'am.

552
00:40:23,735 --> 00:40:25,653
It's currently 4:15 p.m.
STYLE
::cue()

553
00:40:26,362 --> 00:40:27,613
One hour, for three billion.

554
00:40:27,697 --> 00:40:28,948
Keep that in mind.

555
00:40:29,449 --> 00:40:31,075
-[line disconnects]
-[sighs]

556
00:40:34,037 --> 00:40:35,038
[sighs]

557
00:40:41,502 --> 00:40:42,670
Three billion?

558
00:40:57,268 --> 00:40:58,394
Hey.

559
00:41:02,106 --> 00:41:03,900
Can you not hear me?

560
00:41:28,508 --> 00:41:29,509
[sighs]

561
00:41:44,232 --> 00:41:45,233
[grunts]

562
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:48,361
[grunts]

563
00:41:50,780 --> 00:41:51,781
[grunts]

564
00:41:51,864 --> 00:41:52,865
[breathing heavily]

565
00:42:14,762 --> 00:42:15,805
[pulls hand brake]

566
00:42:15,888 --> 00:42:17,348
-[unclasps seat belt]
-[car beeping]

567
00:42:19,684 --> 00:42:21,018
[sighs]

568
00:42:27,150 --> 00:42:28,901
[rattling]

569
00:42:28,985 --> 00:42:30,862
-[thud]
-[footsteps approaching]

570
00:42:30,945 --> 00:42:31,946
[gasps]

571
00:42:44,125 --> 00:42:45,793
-[keys jingling]
-[gasps]

572
00:42:47,253 --> 00:42:48,462
[door unlocking]

573
00:43:11,736 --> 00:43:14,280
[whirring]

574
00:43:15,698 --> 00:43:16,949
[muffled groaning]

575
00:43:19,577 --> 00:43:20,578
Are you all right?

576
00:43:22,079 --> 00:43:23,164
Careful there.

577
00:43:23,831 --> 00:43:25,249
You'll break your ankle.

578
00:43:26,542 --> 00:43:29,003
I wouldn't want my guest to get hurt.

579
00:43:29,086 --> 00:43:30,254
-[metal scraps]
-[yelps]

580
00:43:32,048 --> 00:43:36,969
You know, I was really touched
by your mother's love for you.

581
00:43:38,638 --> 00:43:40,014
My mom?

582
00:43:42,725 --> 00:43:45,978
She's an incredibly generous lady.

583
00:43:48,022 --> 00:43:49,857
No, what am I even saying?

584
00:43:49,941 --> 00:43:51,400
[clears throat] You ready?

585
00:43:55,446 --> 00:43:58,824
Are you ready to say hi to your family?
STYLE
::cue()

586
00:44:03,329 --> 00:44:04,664
[phone buzzing]

587
00:44:04,747 --> 00:44:06,415
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

588
00:44:07,875 --> 00:44:10,836
What? It's been nowhere near an hour.

589
00:44:12,546 --> 00:44:14,715
Ma'am, just do
what you did earlier. Be calm.

590
00:44:21,931 --> 00:44:23,266
[breathes shakily]

591
00:44:28,896 --> 00:44:29,981
UNKNOWN NUMBER

592
00:44:30,481 --> 00:44:31,482
Mom!

593
00:44:31,565 --> 00:44:32,650
Seyun!

594
00:44:33,609 --> 00:44:35,987
Oh, Seyun… Se…

595
00:44:36,612 --> 00:44:39,156
You okay, sweetie? Are you hurt?

596
00:44:40,241 --> 00:44:42,034
-I'm okay.
-[Dr. Ko whimpers]

597
00:44:42,702 --> 00:44:45,371
Oh, look at you, you poor thing.

598
00:44:45,454 --> 00:44:46,831
[Dr. Ko sobbing] Seyun…

599
00:44:46,914 --> 00:44:48,916
-You got him yet?
-[Seyun's mother] I'll take care of it.

600
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,960
Now it says he's in Gansu, China.

601
00:44:51,043 --> 00:44:52,545
Hang in there, okay?

602
00:44:52,628 --> 00:44:54,297
-[crying] Se-Seyun…
-[Seyun] Okay.

603
00:44:55,881 --> 00:44:57,174
Sir?

604
00:44:57,258 --> 00:45:00,594
[driver] Now you've seen
that your daughter's okay, right?

605
00:45:00,678 --> 00:45:05,599
[gasps] Where do we go? Tell us,
and we'll be there with the money.

606
00:45:06,559 --> 00:45:07,601
[chuckling] No, it's fine.

607
00:45:08,686 --> 00:45:11,981
I'll take care of everything, ma'am.
Don't worry about a thing.

608
00:45:12,064 --> 00:45:13,649
Just stay comfortable at home.

609
00:45:15,401 --> 00:45:16,402
[grunts]

610
00:45:17,278 --> 00:45:19,739
Sit on your comfortable couch

611
00:45:20,740 --> 00:45:23,367
-and watch your precious daughter die!
-[grunts]

612
00:45:23,451 --> 00:45:26,495
-Seyun!
-[exclaims] Seyun!

613
00:45:26,579 --> 00:45:27,997
-[Seyun's mother] Wait!
-[Dr. Ko] No!

614
00:45:28,080 --> 00:45:31,876
-Sir! Please, sir!
-No… [whimpers]

615
00:45:31,959 --> 00:45:33,085
Why are you doing this?

616
00:45:33,169 --> 00:45:36,255
Just because you're rich,
you think you can mock me?

617
00:45:37,006 --> 00:45:39,383
No! Not at all!

618
00:45:41,844 --> 00:45:44,055
-No!
-That's not true!

619
00:45:44,138 --> 00:45:46,015
-Stop!
-It's not like that!

620
00:45:46,515 --> 00:45:47,516
-[Dr. Ko] No!
-[gasps]

621
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:48,976
[sobbing]

622
00:45:49,518 --> 00:45:52,229
-Please… I'm sorry!
-Seyun…

623
00:45:52,313 --> 00:45:55,066
You're sorry?
Well, sorry's not going to cut it.

624
00:45:55,149 --> 00:45:57,777
-Please! Please don't! Stop it!
-[Dr. Ko] Let her go!

625
00:45:58,527 --> 00:45:59,528
[driver grunts]

626
00:45:59,612 --> 00:46:02,198
-No, you can't! Please don't do this!
-No, stop it!

627
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:04,241
-Seyun!
-Honey!

628
00:46:04,325 --> 00:46:05,201
[Seyun's mother screams]

629
00:46:06,994 --> 00:46:08,329
[driver grunts]

630
00:46:09,872 --> 00:46:10,873
[grunts]

631
00:46:10,956 --> 00:46:14,627
-[wailing] No! Seyun!
-[sobbing] Seyun…

632
00:46:14,710 --> 00:46:17,088
Please…

633
00:46:17,171 --> 00:46:19,340
-Please… No.
-Seyun…

634
00:46:23,636 --> 00:46:25,096
-No…
-[both sobbing]

635
00:46:32,228 --> 00:46:33,938
[panting]

636
00:46:37,942 --> 00:46:39,276
[Dr. Ko sobbing] Seyun.

637
00:46:42,446 --> 00:46:44,615
[Seyun's mother wailing]

638
00:46:44,698 --> 00:46:45,908
Seyun…

639
00:46:47,284 --> 00:46:49,829
-Se-Se-Seyun?
-Seyun…

640
00:46:49,912 --> 00:46:52,248
[Taeju] Open your eyes, Seyun.

641
00:46:57,837 --> 00:47:01,966
[sobbing] Se-Seyun, wake up, please.

642
00:47:04,677 --> 00:47:05,719
Honey…

643
00:47:10,933 --> 00:47:12,226
Honey…

644
00:47:12,977 --> 00:47:14,270
Honey…

645
00:47:18,357 --> 00:47:20,025
You bastard!

646
00:47:20,109 --> 00:47:22,236
I'm going to kill you!

647
00:47:22,736 --> 00:47:26,031
I'm… I'm going to… [shouts]

648
00:47:26,740 --> 00:47:31,829
I'm going to find you
and tear you to pieces, you bastard!

649
00:47:32,788 --> 00:47:34,165
[sobbing]

650
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:36,125
[coughs]

651
00:47:39,879 --> 00:47:41,297
-Huh?
-[coughs]

652
00:47:42,256 --> 00:47:44,091
Se-Seyun?

653
00:47:44,175 --> 00:47:45,426
-Se-Seyun!
-[Seyun moans]

654
00:47:45,509 --> 00:47:46,802
[coughs]

655
00:47:48,637 --> 00:47:51,640
[stuttering] Look, she's still alive!

656
00:47:51,724 --> 00:47:53,476
-Seyun!
-[gasps]

657
00:47:53,559 --> 00:47:55,603
Seyun!

658
00:47:55,686 --> 00:47:57,188
-Seyun.
-Honey, she's still alive.

659
00:47:57,271 --> 00:47:59,940
-Can you… Can you hear me?
-[Dr. Ko] Seyun!

660
00:48:00,649 --> 00:48:01,817
Mr. Kang.

661
00:48:03,652 --> 00:48:05,321
[shouts] Mr. Kang Taeju!

662
00:48:05,404 --> 00:48:07,072
Wait a second, I…

663
00:48:07,156 --> 00:48:09,909
-What do I do?
-I got it…

664
00:48:09,992 --> 00:48:11,285
Ah, ah, uh.

665
00:48:11,368 --> 00:48:14,497
Yes. sir. It's me again. Please go on.

666
00:48:14,580 --> 00:48:15,581
Listen.

667
00:48:16,373 --> 00:48:19,126
You just had to give me
the money you promised, simple as that.

668
00:48:19,210 --> 00:48:20,211
Right.

669
00:48:20,294 --> 00:48:22,755
Why do you keep making it so complicated?

670
00:48:22,838 --> 00:48:24,006
I made this clear.

671
00:48:24,089 --> 00:48:25,382
I said…

672
00:48:26,342 --> 00:48:28,594
[sighs] I said I'd only talk to you,

673
00:48:28,677 --> 00:48:31,055
but you put those fossils
in charge of the situation.

674
00:48:31,138 --> 00:48:32,681
[sobbing] We're sorry.

675
00:48:32,765 --> 00:48:35,935
I-I'm sorry. I really am.

676
00:48:36,018 --> 00:48:38,896
I said I hate it
when people make things complicated.

677
00:48:39,480 --> 00:48:43,984
And I told you not to call the cops,
but you got not one,

678
00:48:44,527 --> 00:48:49,740
not two, but four pigs
in the house and lied about it.

679
00:48:50,533 --> 00:48:52,535
-He's watching us.
-[driver] Why are you doing this to me?

680
00:48:52,618 --> 00:48:54,078
He might have an accomplice.

681
00:48:54,161 --> 00:48:55,621
-Go look outside.
-I'm on it.

682
00:48:55,704 --> 00:48:58,290
-I'm sorry, it's all my fault!
-Oh, God.

683
00:48:59,458 --> 00:49:02,294
Did you really think
you could fool me that easily?
STYLE
::cue()

684
00:49:02,378 --> 00:49:04,713
No, it's not like that.

685
00:49:04,797 --> 00:49:07,007
This is just a misunderstanding.

686
00:49:07,091 --> 00:49:09,552
My wife's parents called the cops
out of desperation

687
00:49:09,635 --> 00:49:12,721
because they had no idea
about the situation. I had no choice!

688
00:49:12,805 --> 00:49:15,975
-Yes. We're sorry.
-Excuses.

689
00:49:16,058 --> 00:49:19,228
Stupid excuses! I'm sick and tired of it!

690
00:49:20,187 --> 00:49:23,691
I just trusted you

691
00:49:23,774 --> 00:49:27,152
and did exactly what you asked me to do.

692
00:49:28,320 --> 00:49:30,906
So why are you doing this to me?

693
00:49:31,490 --> 00:49:34,118
I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.

694
00:49:34,702 --> 00:49:36,745
You just couldn't
bring yourself to pay me?

695
00:49:36,829 --> 00:49:38,872
Is that why you're doing this?

696
00:49:40,249 --> 00:49:43,043
No. Not at all.
Absolutely nothing like that.

697
00:49:43,127 --> 00:49:44,169
Listen to me.

698
00:49:45,671 --> 00:49:48,215
You're going to pay
for disappointing me until the end.

699
00:49:48,299 --> 00:49:51,927
-No! You can't!
-No!

700
00:49:52,011 --> 00:49:53,804
-No!
-Seyun! No!

701
00:49:53,887 --> 00:49:56,515
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal, boss.

702
00:49:57,725 --> 00:49:59,268
And now, your wife's going to die.

703
00:50:00,936 --> 00:50:03,230
-No, please.
-Hey, Kang Taeju.

704
00:50:04,940 --> 00:50:06,233
This is on you.

705
00:50:07,192 --> 00:50:08,193
CALL ENDED

706
00:50:08,277 --> 00:50:09,278
[stammers]

707
00:50:09,361 --> 00:50:10,863
-Sir! Please!
-[Dr. Ko sobbing] Seyun.

708
00:50:10,946 --> 00:50:13,115
-Don't do this!
-[Seyun's mother wailing]

709
00:50:13,198 --> 00:50:15,701
Oh, Seyun!

710
00:50:16,201 --> 00:50:19,121
No, Seyun!

711
00:50:20,914 --> 00:50:23,751
This is my fault…

712
00:50:35,512 --> 00:50:37,473
Hey, play that last bit back.

713
00:50:38,057 --> 00:50:39,183
Yes, sir.

714
00:50:41,644 --> 00:50:43,854
[driver] …excuses!
I'm sick and tired of it!

715
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:47,733
I just trusted you

716
00:50:47,816 --> 00:50:51,195
and did exactly what you asked me to do.

717
00:50:51,278 --> 00:50:52,446
"What you asked me to do"?

718
00:50:52,529 --> 00:50:54,865
I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.

719
00:50:56,367 --> 00:50:58,494
-[Dosik] Mr. Kang!
-[footsteps approaching]

720
00:51:02,539 --> 00:51:06,418
You're under arrest for solicitation
of kidnapping and murder of Ko Seyun.

721
00:51:06,502 --> 00:51:09,338
You have the right to remain silent.
Your words can and will be

722
00:51:09,421 --> 00:51:11,840
used against you.
You have the right to an attorney.

723
00:51:13,926 --> 00:51:14,927
Come on.

724
00:51:15,010 --> 00:51:17,513
What… Why are you doing this?

725
00:51:17,596 --> 00:51:19,014
We'll talk down at the station.

726
00:51:19,098 --> 00:51:20,474
Wh-What on earth is going on?

727
00:51:20,557 --> 00:51:22,935
Wait a minute. Wait.

728
00:51:24,144 --> 00:51:25,479
What the hell are you doing?

729
00:51:26,730 --> 00:51:27,856
We just got a tip.

730
00:51:29,191 --> 00:51:30,317
What tip?

731
00:51:31,402 --> 00:51:33,946
So I said we should get divorced.

732
00:51:35,197 --> 00:51:36,615
But she said she didn't want to.

733
00:51:36,699 --> 00:51:39,034
Well, she said she'd never do it.

734
00:51:39,743 --> 00:51:40,994
[driver] Why's that?

735
00:51:41,829 --> 00:51:43,122
Because it's what I want.

736
00:51:43,205 --> 00:51:45,833
She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.

737
00:51:47,876 --> 00:51:49,378
[driver] I just trusted you…

738
00:51:49,461 --> 00:51:52,548
-[phone buzzing]
-…and did exactly what you asked me to do.

739
00:51:53,507 --> 00:51:54,591
Yeah, talk.

740
00:51:55,884 --> 00:51:56,885
What?

741
00:51:56,969 --> 00:52:01,724
[driver] Good afternoon,
I have a tip about a renowned neurosurgeon

742
00:52:02,391 --> 00:52:06,270
soliciting the murder of his own wife.

743
00:52:07,730 --> 00:52:11,483
[Taeju] She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.

744
00:52:11,567 --> 00:52:14,570
Wait, isn't that your voice?

745
00:52:14,653 --> 00:52:16,947
[Taeju] I'm out of options now.

746
00:52:17,030 --> 00:52:20,117
[sighs] Taeju, what am I hearing?

747
00:52:20,826 --> 00:52:22,703
[Taeju] Anyway, that being said…

748
00:52:25,414 --> 00:52:29,793
I want you to get rid of my wife.

749
00:52:30,461 --> 00:52:31,754
[driver] What did you say?

750
00:52:32,421 --> 00:52:34,465
[Taeju] Get rid of my wife.

751
00:52:35,966 --> 00:52:37,342
I'll pay you, okay?

752
00:52:38,761 --> 00:52:40,763
I'll pay you 300… No.

753
00:52:40,846 --> 00:52:43,682
-I'll pay you 500 million won.
-[Dr. Ko gasps]

754
00:52:44,266 --> 00:52:45,476
So please.

755
00:52:48,020 --> 00:52:49,855
Father, it's not what it looks like.

756
00:52:49,938 --> 00:52:52,232
-I can explain everything. Believe me!
-Take him.

757
00:52:52,316 --> 00:52:53,650
-Come on.
-What's going on?

758
00:52:53,734 --> 00:52:55,027
Say something!

759
00:52:55,110 --> 00:52:57,196
-Father, I can explain everything!
-Get moving!

760
00:52:57,279 --> 00:53:00,491
You bastard!

761
00:53:02,367 --> 00:53:03,827
-Take him to the station.
-Got it.

762
00:53:03,911 --> 00:53:05,829
[♪ dramatic music playing]
STYLE
::cue()

763
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:01,134
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

764
00:54:01,218 --> 00:54:02,845
TAKING ACCOUNTABILITY
FOR THE PEOPLE

765
00:54:04,805 --> 00:54:05,806
[thud]

766
00:54:06,723 --> 00:54:07,766
[Dosik] Mr. Kang.

767
00:54:09,768 --> 00:54:11,562
How do you know the kidnapper?

768
00:54:12,771 --> 00:54:14,189
I don't know him.

769
00:54:15,107 --> 00:54:17,609
He showed up when I called for a driver.

770
00:54:17,693 --> 00:54:19,570
So you solicited

771
00:54:20,696 --> 00:54:22,906
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

772
00:54:23,907 --> 00:54:25,784
I never solicited anything.

773
00:54:27,786 --> 00:54:32,207
[Taeju through laptop]
I want you to get rid of my wife.

774
00:54:32,291 --> 00:54:34,001
[driver] What? What did you say?

775
00:54:34,585 --> 00:54:36,253
[Taeju] Get rid of my wife.

776
00:54:36,336 --> 00:54:38,338
I'll pay you, okay?

777
00:54:39,256 --> 00:54:41,675
-I'll pay you 300… No.
-So what did you mean by that?

778
00:54:41,758 --> 00:54:44,261
I'll pay you 500 million won.

779
00:54:44,344 --> 00:54:45,929
-So please.
-Well… [sighs]

780
00:54:46,013 --> 00:54:50,726
I was drunk out of my mind at that time.

781
00:54:55,647 --> 00:55:00,861
Honestly, I don't really remember.
And I don't know why I said that.

782
00:55:02,696 --> 00:55:04,698
You know where Ms. Ko is, don't you?

783
00:55:05,407 --> 00:55:06,992
Is she with your accomplice?

784
00:55:08,118 --> 00:55:09,536
-[sighs]
-Mr. Kang Taeju.

785
00:55:09,620 --> 00:55:11,830
Mr. Kang, where's your accomplice?

786
00:55:12,372 --> 00:55:13,373
[stammers, sighs]

787
00:55:14,291 --> 00:55:16,335
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

788
00:55:16,418 --> 00:55:18,295
Tell us. You know where she is!

789
00:55:18,378 --> 00:55:20,631
I said I don't know!

790
00:55:26,720 --> 00:55:29,514
The… Yes, the tip you got.

791
00:55:29,598 --> 00:55:31,475
I'm sure it's from him.

792
00:55:31,558 --> 00:55:34,311
You can just track the IP or something.

793
00:55:34,394 --> 00:55:38,190
IP says that email
came from Nanning, China.

794
00:55:41,026 --> 00:55:42,653
You didn't see this coming, did you?

795
00:55:42,736 --> 00:55:44,404
Your accomplice…

796
00:55:44,488 --> 00:55:47,574
He's way more dangerous than you think.

797
00:55:47,658 --> 00:55:49,826
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

798
00:55:54,081 --> 00:55:55,707
Like I told you, I have no idea.

799
00:55:59,044 --> 00:56:01,296
Don't do this, man.

800
00:56:02,047 --> 00:56:03,131
Just be honest.

801
00:56:03,757 --> 00:56:05,217
Where's Ms. Ko?

802
00:56:06,134 --> 00:56:07,135
I don't know.

803
00:56:08,261 --> 00:56:10,639
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

804
00:56:11,431 --> 00:56:13,392
You're losing time here!

805
00:56:14,351 --> 00:56:18,188
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

806
00:56:18,271 --> 00:56:21,858
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

807
00:56:21,942 --> 00:56:23,026
Calm down, Mr. Kang.

808
00:56:23,110 --> 00:56:27,155
I'm serious!
There's no time to be screwing around!

809
00:56:27,239 --> 00:56:28,740
-[Dosik] Mr. Kang!
-[grunts]

810
00:56:29,658 --> 00:56:30,992
[groans, grunting]

811
00:56:35,831 --> 00:56:36,832
Calm now?

812
00:56:43,046 --> 00:56:45,674
[person] Hey, say something.

813
00:56:47,175 --> 00:56:49,469
Don't leave me here all by myself.

814
00:57:02,983 --> 00:57:05,527
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

815
00:57:05,610 --> 00:57:06,778
That one doesn't work.

816
00:57:06,862 --> 00:57:07,988
Use the next one.

817
00:57:14,119 --> 00:57:15,120
What the hell?
STYLE
::cue()

818
00:57:17,456 --> 00:57:20,792
Man, it's about time
they fix this place up.

819
00:57:20,876 --> 00:57:23,003
Nothing works in here.

820
00:57:23,503 --> 00:57:24,755
[phone buzzing]

821
00:57:27,758 --> 00:57:29,509
Oh, hey, Captain Kim.

822
00:57:29,593 --> 00:57:31,970
Yeah. [laughing] It's been too long.

823
00:57:32,637 --> 00:57:34,556
Oh, that? Yeah, it was really helpful.

824
00:57:34,639 --> 00:57:36,224
Take your time, okay?

825
00:57:36,308 --> 00:57:39,311
Right, I was going to come and see you.

826
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:41,730
[laughing]

827
00:57:51,740 --> 00:57:53,283
Damn it.

828
00:57:53,366 --> 00:57:54,367
[sighs]

829
00:58:02,167 --> 00:58:04,669
[officers grumbling]

830
00:58:04,753 --> 00:58:06,838
-What the hell, man?
-[officer] Hey, come over here!

831
00:58:06,922 --> 00:58:08,423
What's that? No, not you.

832
00:58:08,507 --> 00:58:10,592
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

833
00:58:13,136 --> 00:58:15,639
I don't have time to waste here.

834
00:58:17,140 --> 00:58:20,185
I didn't do it, but everyone thinks I did.

835
00:58:21,686 --> 00:58:23,605
No one believes me.

836
00:58:24,731 --> 00:58:26,024
[stranger] Who would?

837
00:58:30,320 --> 00:58:31,738
No one believes you.

838
00:58:33,198 --> 00:58:35,450
Why would anyone believe you, Mr. Kang?

839
00:58:40,747 --> 00:58:41,957
Who are you?

840
00:58:47,254 --> 00:58:48,296
What do you want?

841
00:58:51,758 --> 00:58:52,759
[shushes]

842
00:58:53,552 --> 00:58:55,136
I said, who are you?

843
00:58:55,679 --> 00:59:00,809
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

844
00:59:02,894 --> 00:59:03,895
What?

845
00:59:13,363 --> 00:59:18,201
THE HUSBAND

846
00:59:18,285 --> 00:59:20,370
[♪ closing theme song playing]

847
00:59:58,325 --> 01:00:01,786
[stranger] If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong.

848
01:00:01,870 --> 01:00:03,538
Remember. Get there by 11 p.m.

849
01:00:03,622 --> 01:00:04,664
[Hyeonsu] Mr. Kang!

850
01:00:04,748 --> 01:00:05,874
[Dosik] Get him!

851
01:00:06,374 --> 01:00:09,878
[news anchor] Police took over 20 minutes
to arrive, allowing the suspect to escape.

852
01:00:09,961 --> 01:00:13,131
How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

853
01:00:13,214 --> 01:00:14,215
It wasn't you, was it?

854
01:00:14,299 --> 01:00:16,718
[Taeju] Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.

855
01:00:16,801 --> 01:00:17,844
-Stay away!
-[screams]

856
01:00:17,928 --> 01:00:20,889
[officer] Visual on suspect vehicle.
Requesting backup.

857
01:00:22,682 --> 01:00:24,601
[driver] This is how much time
you have left.

858
01:00:24,684 --> 01:00:27,812
-When the sand runs out, you're dead.
-[screams, sobs]

859
01:00:27,896 --> 01:00:29,814
[Taeju] I have to save Seyun.

860
01:00:30,315 --> 01:00:32,317
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon

